#: ../../src/config/proxying.rst:25
msgid "CouchDB As Proxy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/config/proxying.rst:27
msgid ""
"The HTTP proxy feature makes it easy to map and redirect different content "
"through your CouchDB URL. The proxy works by mapping a pathname and passing "
"all content after that prefix through to the configured proxy address."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/config/proxying.rst:32
msgid ""
"Configuration of the proxy redirect is handled through the "
"``[httpd_global_handlers]`` section of the CouchDB configuration file "
"(typically ``local.ini``). The format is::"
